Cell.Text: Before my father became obsessed with the prophecy, mother and I spent quite a bit of time together. | She was very fond of her alchemical garden in the castle courtyard. She taught me quite a bit about cultivating quality reagents.
Like the best of friends. I would never hesitate to share anything with her.

Sadly, yes. It was very sudden. It was almost like one day we were a normal family, and then the next I didn't know who they were. | I'd try to visit my mother in the garden, and she'd quickly shoo me away saying she was much to busy.
She had to be up to something in that garden. I'm hoping it's a clue that will tell us where she went.
If I had to guess, I'd say the moment mother fled the castle, father went on a rampage. | Knowing him, anything at all that represented my mother was destroyed.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ04RNPCCourtyardBranchTopic: What happened to the castle courtyard?

Cell.Text: It appears that way. I suppose he wanted to put the past behind him. | Perhaps if he had spent more time with us, he would have recognized the beauty for himself.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ04RNPCCourtyardBranchTopic01: Then he just walled it off.

Cell.Text: The Soul Cairn is a tiny sliver of Oblivion, the realm of the daedra. | It's ruled by unseen beings known as the Ideal Masters.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ04RNPCSoulCairnBranchTopic: Anything you can tell me about the Soul Cairn?

Cell.Text: [S] Honestly, I'm not certain. I can only guess that the souls trapped there hold some sort of interest to necromancers.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ04RNPCSoulCairnBranchTopic01: Why was your mother so fascinated by it?

Cell.Text: Extremely little is known about them. | As far as I've heard, no one's seen them and returned to Tamriel to describe what they look like.

I've read tales in some of mother's books. Stories about necromancers that have successfully communed with the Ideal Masters. | The fools made illicit deals with the beings, trading souls for the ability to summon the undead.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ04RNPCSoulCairnIdealMastersBranchTopic01: Then how are you sure they even exist?

Cell.Text: Because the majority of the tales end with the Ideal Masters duping the necromancers who end up either dead, or worse.
I had no idea that her laboratory even existed. | I knew she kept a small alchemy setup in her drawing room, but nothing that even comes close to what she's created in these ruins.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ04RNPCLaboatoryBranchTopic: Your mother maintained quite a laboratory.

Cell.Text: Judging from the equipment and the nature of the ingredients, I'd say she was expanding her knowledge of necromancy.
I don't know. Certainly not longevity. Being a vampire, she already had that handled quite well I'd say.

Well, as far as I'm aware it's the only one in existence. | The previous owners of the castle had a sundial in the courtyard, and obviously that didn't appeal to my mother. | She persuaded an elven artisan to make some improvements. You can see the inlaid plates that show the phases of the moons, Masser and Secunda.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ04RNPCMoondialTLBranchTopic: What's so special about the moondial?

Cell.Text: That's the thing... what's the point of a moondial? I always wondered why she didn't just have the whole thing ripped out. | But she loved it. I don't know. I guess it's like having a piece of art, if you're into that sort of thing.
[S] Hard to say. Maybe if we found the missing crests, we could play with it a little.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ04RNPCMoondialTLBranchTopic02: So what exactly am I doing to it?
